gently:** If the fear feels uncontrollable, consider reaching out to a crisis hotline like the National Alliance on Mental Illness (NAMI) helpline at 1-800-950-6264 (in the US) or a similar service in your area for immediate support. They can help bridge to mental health resources, and sometimes just talking it out with a specialist can make a difference while you pursue evaluation.\n- **Symptom support in the meantime:** If you haven't already, try lying down with an eye mask and noise-canceling headphones to block out stimuli. Over-the-counter options like a migraine cocktail (ibuprofen + acetaminophen + caffeine) might offer more relief\u2014check with a pharmacist if needed.\n\nIs there anyone close to you who can accompany you to the doctor or ER for support? Or any other details about your symptoms (like recent stressors or changes in vision) that might help paint a fuller picture? You're not alone in this fight\u2014let's get you the concrete help you deserve so you can start feeling like yourself again. I'm here if you need to vent or plan your next step. Take care."
