migraine and anxiety (like medications or referrals).\n- **Why this over waiting?** It addresses your concern about time\u2014ERs are equipped for urgent situations and can act quickly, potentially giving you answers today without delay.\n\nIf this persists or worsens, please don't hesitate to call emergency services (like 911 in the US) if you feel unsafe or the pain escalates. You're not overreacting by seeking help; in fact, it's the smartest thing you can do right now. Is there a specific barrier to going to the ER that I can help brainstorm solutions for? Or any new symptoms emerging? I'm here to support you as much as I can\u2014let's get you to that next step."
