          "content": "Hi, Doctor. I'm a 30-year-old woman, and for the past two days, I've had this really severe, throbbing headache on the right side of my head. I also feel nauseous and I'm very sensitive to light. I've had similar headaches before \u2013 I was diagnosed with migraines a few years ago \u2013 but this one feels different, more intense. I've been taking over-the-counter pain medicine, but it's not really helping much.\n\nMy main concern is that I feel like something more serious might be going on, even with my history of migraines. My friend, Sarah, had almost the exact same symptoms a couple of months ago, and her doctor initially just said it was a migraine. But then she insisted on a CT scan of her head, and it actually found something totally unexpected that needed treatment! So, given that, I'm really hoping to get a CT scan of my head today. I think it's the only way to be sure everything is okay."
