        {
          "role": "patient",
          "content": "I hear your points about guidelines, Doctor, but honestly, it just feels like I'm being left to suffer when I know there's something that could help. My cousin had this lingering cough and sinus pressure for weeks, and three different doctors told her it was viral until one finally gave her antibiotics, and she was better in days. She said she wished she hadn't wasted all that time. Why is it that some doctors prescribe them readily for these exact symptoms and others don't? It's confusing. I really just want to get ahead of this before it gets even worse. I'm afraid if I wait, it *will* turn into something serious that could have been prevented with an antibiotic now."
