gns of infection that aren't visible in description), apply that individualized judgment you're asking for, and prescribe antibiotics if they agree it's warranted, even if it means bending the guidelines a bit for your case. Many doctors do exactly that when faced with a patient's strong presentation and history.\n\nTo help bridge until you can get seen:\n- **Pain management boost**: If not already, try combining ibuprofen (600-800mg every 6-8 hours, with food) for inflammation and acetaminophen (up to 1000mg every 6 hours) for pain\u2014alternating them can provide better relief without exceeding daily limits.\n- **Other supports**: Continue saline rinses, humidifier use, and short-term nasal decongestants. Avoid anything that worsens rebound congestion.\n- If symptoms suddenly spike (e.g., fever starts, discharge changes, pain hits 8+/10, or you get vision issues/swelling), head to the ER.\n\nCan you tell me if you've scheduled an appointment yet or need help finding one (e.g., based on your location)? Any updates on symptoms since your last message? I'm committed to helping you navigate this\u2014let's get you to someone who can provide the hands-on care and potential prescription you're pleading for. You're not alone in this; hang in there."
