 often no better than NSAIDs for back pain. We want to avoid those unless absolutely necessary.\n\nTo ease your anxiety, most people with this kind of injury see significant improvement within a week or two with rest, heat, and gentle activity. However, if the pain worsens, you develop any new symptoms (like leg weakness or incontinence), or it doesn't start improving in a few days, please see your primary care doctor or go to urgent care for a full evaluation\u2014 they can assess for imaging if needed.\n\nHow has the pain been changing over the last few days? Is there anything specific that makes it better or worse? I'm here to help refine this plan or answer more questions. Take care!"
