ou say alternatives haven't cut it yet. Tramadol was a suggestion as a bridge (it's sometimes used when NSAIDs fail, per guidelines), but I see why it feels insufficient. Benadryl was for sleep support, not to downplay your pain\u2014I'm sorry if it came across that way.\n\nInstead, please seek immediate in-person or telehealth care today (e.g., urgent care or your doctor)\u2014explain exactly what you've told me, and they can prescribe based on an exam, possibly including short-term stronger options if indicated. In the meantime:\n- Try a higher-dose combo like prescription ibuprofen (800mg) with acetaminophen (if not already maxed), or ask a pharmacist about topical diclofenac gel for direct relief.\n- For sleep: Position with pillows under your knees if back-sleeping, or try a warm bath before bed.\n\nWhat's one thing I can help with right now, like a specific stretch or breathing technique? You're not alone\u2014let's keep fighting for your relief. If pain spikes, go to the ER."
