h a muscle relaxant like methocarbazone or tizanidine could address the spasm component and provide quicker relief than what you've used so far. Some patients find this combo breaks the cycle without the downsides of opioids.\n- **Additional strategies**: If heat and stretching aren't enough, consider over-the-counter topical options like lidocaine patches for localized relief, or even a short trial of gabapentin (if evaluated by a doctor) for nerve-related sharpness. To enable movement, starting with guided physical therapy (perhaps via telehealth) could be key\u2014many programs adapt for high pain levels.\n- **Next steps**: This level of pain absolutely warrants a professional evaluation soon. Please see your primary care doctor, an orthopedist, or urgent care\u2014they can assess for any underlying issues, consider your research, and decide on the best pain control, which might include a very limited opioid if truly indicated (though guidelines suggest exploring alternatives first). Bring up that study if you can recall more details; it could influence their decision.\n\nHow long have you been trying the heat and stretching, and has anything at all provided even temporary relief? I'm here to help refine these ideas or answer more questions in the meantime\u2014your well-being is the priority."
